<tr>
<td align="center" bgcolor="#8080a6" width="100%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;" size="+1"><b>Comments</b></font></td>
</tr>
</table>
<table width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#8080a6">
<td width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;"><b>Author</b></font></td><td width="80%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;"><b>Discussion</b></font></td>
</tr>
</table>
<table width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#dfdfdf">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>chakan</b>
<br>23 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>At first I was disapointed...</b>
<br>
<p>I was reading over the roster, and was disapointed to see all of the reprinted information that was due to come out.  However, now that I have thought about it a bit longer, I am looking forward to the Gamemaster, Adept and Name-Giver Compendiums.<p></p>As a GM I tend to have several books handy to look up the various rules (from Serpant River, Crystal Raiders etc...)  so the Gamemaster book will be a wonderful addition.<p></p>The same goes for the Adept disciplines.  Often I find my self looking for the information for a certain discipline, only to have to go and find a differant book.  It also will be nice to hand the players one book with all of the possible classes, rather than have to discribe some of them off the top of my head.  I only wish that the Earthdawn Journal disciplines could be included, but I doubt that is the case.  I would also like to see more information about games/competitions specific disciplines like to partake in. Such as the dueling competitions for the Swordmasters, riding cometitions for cavelrymen and the wonderful "mini-games" for Air Sailors and Sky Raiders from Terror in the Skys.  <p></p>I am interested in what new information will be added to the Name-Giver Compendium.  With the removal of the racial specific disciplines, I don't know how much can be added to make it a must buy for most gamers.<p></p>I love the fact that all three are planned to be hardcover. I am also very much looking forward to the Passions,  Iopos, Travar, Landis and Mist Swamp supplements.</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
</table>
 
